===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|feer|lang=enm}}, {{term|fere|lang=enm}}, {{term|fer|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|fǣr}}, {{m|ang|ġefǣr||calamity, sudden danger, peril, sudden attack, terrible sight}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*fērą||danger}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*per-||to attempt, try, research, risk}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|gevaar||danger, risk, peril|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Gefahr||danger, risk, hazard|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|fara||danger, risk, peril|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|perīculum||danger, risk, trial}},  Albanian {{term|frikë||fear,danger|lang=sq}}.

The verb is from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|feren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|fǣran||to frighten, raven}}, from the noun.

